K pf-531_ pf-lg-hide"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-532_ pf-bg-lazy"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-533_ pf-heading-2-h2">Hydrosol FAQ</h2></div></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-16db" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-535_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><a data-pf-type="Button2" class="sc-emIqIH hFkfQE pf-536_">Explore Our Hydrosols</a></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-5680" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-538_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-539_ pf-heading-2-h3">Hydrosol FAQ</h3></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-f5e0" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-541_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-542_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-543_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-2d908cca-9c02-4578-83bb-8020003e51b8"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Hydrosols are some of the most versatile and gentle plant products you can use—but they are&nbsp;also still a bit of a secret. Whether you're wondering how they’re made, how to use them, or how to keep them fresh, this is where you’ll find the answers.</span></p></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-4c52" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-546_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div class="sc-gOqwAI jjtufm pf-547_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-548_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-549_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="1466aecb-2845-49c2-9707-dcf61e7fcc9a" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Are hydrosols safe to use on skin?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-551_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-552_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-553_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-1e7fcc9a-56bc-413f-b38b-b3ece61b3af1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Yes, hydrosols are safe for most skin types, including sensitive or reactive skin. Because they’re water-based and contain only trace amounts of essential oil, they’re much gentler than pure oils. Still, it’s best to patch-test new products and use high-quality, preservative-free hydrosols like Oshadhi’s.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-556_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-557_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="65cc3de1-2914-46ae-8b28-4579c2d707dc" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>What are the benefits of using hydrosols in skincare?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-559_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-560_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-561_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-07dcf61e-7fcc-4a56-bc31-3f338bb3ece6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Hydrosols naturally hydrate, soothe, and balance the skin without any synthetic ingredients. They can help calm irritation, support skin regeneration, and provide a gentle plant-based aroma that uplifts the mood. They’re also versatile—perfect as toners, facial mists, or after-sun refreshers.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-564_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-565_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="4579c2d7-07dc-461e-bfcc-9a56bc313f33" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>How do I choose the right hydrosol for my skin type?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-567_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-568_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-569_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-9a56bc31-3f33-4bb3-ace6-1b3af142339e"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Choose your hydrosol based on what your skin needs: <strong>rose</strong> or l<strong>avender</strong> for sensitive or dry skin, <strong>witch hazel</strong> or <strong>rosemary</strong> for oily or acne-prone skin, and <strong>chamomile</strong> or <strong>melissa </strong>for soothing redness. You can also choose based on the emotional effect—uplifting, calming, or grounding. It’s perfectly okay to use more than one depending on your mood or the season.</span></p></div></div></div></details></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-90ca" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-572_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div class="sc-gOqwAI jjtufm pf-573_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-574_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-575_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="338bb3ec-e61b-4af1-8233-9ee744120145" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Which hydrosols are best for sensitive skin?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-577_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-578_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-579_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-42efd92c-3015-4a6e-a9b9-e4e56051a292"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Gentle hydrosols like <strong>rose</strong>, <strong>lavender</strong>, <strong>blue chamomile</strong>, and <strong>melissa (lemon balm)</strong> are ideal for calming and hydrating sensitive or irritated skin. They reduce redness, soothe inflammation, and are safe enough for everyday use. Always look for pure, additive-free hydrosols for best results.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-582_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-583_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="1b3af142-339e-4744-9201-45dda590ca67" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>What is the best hydrosol for acne-prone skin?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-585_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-586_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-587_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-e8f59bbc-cad2-43a1-a8a5-e032ebb13740"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">For acne-prone skin, try <strong>witch hazel</strong>, <strong>thyme (linalool)</strong>, <strong>rosemary</strong> <strong>verbenone</strong>, or <strong>bay laurel </strong>hydrosols. These help tone the skin, balance oil production, and gently purify without drying. Apply them as a toner or mist after cleansing.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-590_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-591_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="9ee74412-0145-4da5-90ca-67ee6c823cf3" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Can hydrosols be used as a toner?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-593_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-594_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-595_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5e8cb665-c16d-4ec1-a6e4-da9f7c1dfadc"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Yes! Hydrosols make excellent toners. They help balance the skin’s pH, tighten pores, and deliver gentle plant nutrients—all without alcohol or harsh ingredients.</span></p></div></div></div></details></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-28a3" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-598_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div class="sc-gOqwAI jjtufm pf-599_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-600_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-601_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="1628a32c-c013-45d1-987f-9e975e7783c9" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>How long do hydrosols last?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-603_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-604_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-605_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c01375d1-d87f-4e97-9e77-83c98fcafe16"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Most hydrosols last <strong>6 to 12 months</strong> if stored properly. Once opened, they’re best used within 6 months and kept away from heat and direct light. If the scent changes or it appears cloudy, it’s time to replace it.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-608_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-609_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="d87f9e97-5e77-43c9-8fca-fe168ac0dbe9" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Which hydrosol is best for calming anxiety?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-611_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-612_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-613_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5e7783c9-8fca-4e16-8ac0-dbe9801ac280"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Hydrosols like <strong>neroli</strong>, <strong>lavender</strong>, <strong>chamomile</strong>, and <strong>melissa</strong> are known for their calming effects on the nervous system. Mist them on your face, pillow, or into the air to promote relaxation and reduce stress. Their aroma is gentle but deeply supportive for emotional balance.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-616_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-617_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="8fcafe16-8ac0-4be9-801a-c280bb60c220" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span> Can I use hydrosols in DIY skincare products?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-619_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-620_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-621_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8ac0dbe9-801a-4280-bb60-c2206af3427c"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Absolutely. Hydrosols make a great base for facial masks, creams, body sprays, and more. They add both skin benefits and a light natural scent—just make sure you’re using fresh, pure hydrosols for best results.</span></p></div></div></div></details></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-e999" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-624_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div class="sc-gOqwAI jjtufm pf-625_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-626_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-627_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="88d6e2b8-5eba-4efb-b1d0-094265e5e364" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Should I refrigerate my hydrosol?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-629_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-630_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-631_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5ebaaefb-b1d0-4942-a5e5-e36476d24699"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Yes—refrigeration helps preserve freshness, especially after opening. It also gives you an extra refreshing experience when you mist! Just keep the cap closed tight and avoid contamination.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-634_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-635_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="20e999f7-c9c2-474b-88d6-e2b85ebaaefb" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Are hydrosols safe for babies or during pregnancy?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-637_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-638_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-639_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c9c2d74b-88d6-42b8-9eba-aefbb1d00942"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Many hydrosols—like <strong>lavender</strong>, <strong>chamomile</strong>, and <strong>rose</strong>—are gentle enough for babies and supportive during pregnancy. However, always consult a qualified practitioner if you’re unsure, and avoid stronger varieties unless advised.</span></p></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-dGVrNp kIZjuh pf-642_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-deEcaK pLXxN pf-643_ pf-bg-lazy pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="b1d00942-65e5-4364-b6d2-469906324399" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Where to buy organic hydrosols online?</span></div></summary><div class="sc-lmEGMn dTrJQN pf-645_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-goWbVR iRUUKk pf-646_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-647_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-65e5e364-76d2-4699-8632-439961f719b1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">You can find high-quality, organic hydrosols directly on our webshop at oshadhi.com. We offer a wide selection of over 50 pure plant waters—each tested for quality and crafted with care.</span></p></div></div></div></details></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-6dc5" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-650_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div data-pf-type="Table2" class="sc-heWFv bjKrPl pf-651_"><table class="pf-table-inner"><colgroup data-pf-type="Table2.ColumnBody" class="sc-bNdoSu cDPZuE 